{
  "version": "2.0",
  "note": "Keysight families are the canonical base. Other vendors use 'inherits' + 'overrides': a key replacing an existing parent command = dialect override; null = command not supported on this device (removed); a key not present in the parent = vendor-specific extension (added). Placeholders use Python str.format(): {ch}=channel (1-indexed), {value}=numeric, {voltage}, {current}, {freq}=Hz, {amp}=amplitude, {offset}=DC offset V, {unit}=VPP|VRMS|DBM, {func}=SIN|SQU|RAMP|PULS|NOIS|DC, {coupling}=AC|DC|GND, {slope}=POS|NEG|EITH, {attenuation}=probe ratio, {label}=string max 10 chars, {text}=annotation string. Command spec: plain string=write; [...]= sequential steps; {query:...}=query returning value; {write:...,query:...}=settable+readable; {raw_query:...}=binary read via read_raw().",

  "families": [

    {
